            <scopecontent id="aspace_4cbdb00a88678dd4f7aae49c7bee0984">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>This accession contains zines produced as part of the Chicano lowrider sub-culture during the 1970s and 1980s in California and Texas.</p>
               <p>Included in the materials are three issues of <title>
                     <part>New Lowrider News Bulletin</part>
                  </title>--a magazine edited, designed, and illustrated by Biney Ruiz, a historian from San Jose. Also included in this accession is an issue of <title>
                     <part>Cholo</part>
                  </title>, a publication from San Francisco which features comics and illustrations by Rojelio del Fuego and Ed Silvera and an issue of <title>
                     <part>Latin Life</part>
                  </title> with art and design by David Gonzales.</p>
            </scopecontent>
